==English==

===Alternative forms===
* [[Academe]]

===Etymology===
* From {{etyl|NL.}} {{term|academia|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|Ἀκαδημία|tr=Akadēmia|lang=grc}}; see {{term|academy|lang=en}}. ''Academe'' (frequently capitalized) is a poetic name for the garden or grove near ancient Athens where {{w|Plato}} taught, supposedly named for its former owner, the hero Ἀκάδημος (''{{w|Akademos}};'' Ἑκάδημος, ''Hekademos'').
* First attested in the 1580's.
* {{sense|scholarly life, environment, or community}} First attested in 1849.
* {{sense|lower case}}  First attested in 1956.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈækədiːm/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæk.ə.ˌdim/}}
*: {{rhymes|iːm}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|poetic|}} An [[academy]]; a place of learning.
